column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Visibility down because of pine pollen.
Rather heavy weed growth at rather heavy weed growth at east end of lake.  Heavier than the average year.
More brown because of recent rains through to swamps.
I think the lake turned over.  Very green with pollen on algae.  Lost 2' of visibility in one week.
Large pollen grains in lake.  Last report.
Much less clear that this time last year.
Hot weather-causing algae blooms late this year.

Ice off May 10. water level 6" high because of heavy ice melt. Water very murky from fresh wash of swamp tannic acid + higher levels of water. starting to clear now. (1994-95 winter-no snow-clean water.)
Lots of pine pollen on water.
One eagle.  Severe storm night of June 24- 1997.  Scattered clouds- choppy water.
Lake has turned over and is getting quite clear.
Very nice. Clear to 6' since they (the DNR) took out the upstream dam.

Algae starting to clear out. This lake's clarity improved a great deal this summer since they took out the upstream dam on the Deerskin Flowage. Much less algae growth on dock ladder. Better swimming!
Dark from all the rain. Water 2" higher
Observed good amount of floating weed fragments due to heavy boat traffic. Saw 2 eagles and 1 loon.
Water dark from a lot of rain
Loon and eagle sighting.  Bloom on water.
Fairly clear. No algae this year. Upstream removal of the deerskin dam allows a lot more flow through the lake. Better water quality I think.
lots of boat traffic week of memorial day water temp
Very dark this spring. Starting to clear.
fair amount of pine pollen on water. may fly hatch in

column1: progress. Many snails in quiet areas along shore

column2: extreme amount of pine pollen and dead mayflies on

column1: water surface. several cluthes of malards sighted.

column2: heavy algae bloom/pine pollen on water
boat traffic falling off. kids back to school soon.

column1: secchi reading deepest of year at 6'.

column2: Clearer than usual. The rain helped to flush out the hazy water.
turn over taking place. heavy algea bloom
Last reading this fall. Cold and cloudy.
disollved oxygen 8ppm. nitrates less then 5ppm. phosphate 1-2 ppm. ph 8 . coliform negative. dto-40jtu
pine pollen in full swing; mayfly hatch starting

coliform test negative.  turbidity 40jtu.  nitrate test less then 5 ppm.  phosphate 1-2 ppm. ph 8. took water sample home to conduct tests. 1st time dissolved oxygen was not 8ppm was 4 ppm instead. Delay in testing probably a factor
Very murky. Very low reading at 4.5'. Water temp the week before were approaching 60 degrees. Pan fishing was great .Walleyes and perch are spawned out. and water temp have dropped 10 to 13 degrees
Lake has cleared somewhat since last reading.  Good walleye catches.
Worst secchi readings sice starting to collect data

Heavy boat traffic on Eagle River chain. Noticed significant fragments of Eurasian milfoil on water surface. Many jet skis and boats driving through milfoil beds. Lower then normal sechi reading 4 '    Due to boat traffic and algae bloom

column1: Dissolved Oxygen: Between 4 And 8 PPM on color scale 73 % oxygen saturation at 24 celcius.Fair to good

column2: Worst Secchi readings since started collecting data
Water clarity + Secchi reading improved slightly. Lot of boat traffic. need enforcement on jet ski's with no regard to no wake areas and distance from shorelines.
Additional chemical test results as follows: Turbidity 40 JTU. Phosphate 1 PPM( very good) Nitrates 5 PPM (good to excellent) PH 7-8 (good to excellent.

column1: After heavy boat traffic over holiday weekend a great amount of eurasian millfoil fragments around peir. People need to recognize where beds are and stay out of them

column2: Boat traffic has slowed. Only 3 boats on whole lake this Monday 9/26/05
Ice out early on 4-13-06. Perch spawning in full swing at ice out.
2 nest sites for eagles on lake this year

Lake association installed 12 no wake bouys atound existing millfoil beds to prevent boat traffic from fragmenting eurasian millfoil and spreading of the same.Cost to assoc . in excess of $1700.00 plus no charge labor.Additional tests conducted: Turbidity:40 JTU- Phospate: 1ppm- Nitrate 5ppm- ph 7.
calm and overcast conditions improved secchi readings by 1 foot

column1: Lake association installed no wake bouys around heavy milfoil beds. milfoi is very heay in certain spots. waiting for a completed lake survey by northern enviromental. will decide action plan after seeing their report

column2: milfoil beds on north and east end of lake worst ever. water has good amount of algea. lake in state of turnover
